  displayName: Tiyanak
  description: In numerous Philippine tales, the tiyanak appears in infant-like form
    to exploit compassion before revealing a predatory nature. Accounts differ by
    region, but many emphasize sudden shifts from helplessness to violence. The figure
    is often interpreted as a cautionary symbol about deceptive appearances, misplaced
    trust, and the vulnerability of those who ignore warning signs.
